Hungary Gives $20 Million Photovoltaics Aid, Vilaggazdasag Says

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-05-26T11:06:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/hungary-gives-20-million-photovoltaics-aid-vilaggazdasag-says.html
Hungary granted 3.75 billion forint
($20 million) in subsidies to 36 applicants for investments in
photovoltaic plants in recent months, newspaper  Vilaggazdasag 
reported today.  The funds will help increase peak capacity by almost 7
megawatts from 0.9 megawatts, the newspaper said, citing Janos Bencsik, state secretary at the Development Ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  